  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "69 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0ba8\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "69 lakh people curse the president from the streets - Nalin Bandara",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is completely wrong to mention that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has Lok Sabha. 69 lakh people are cursing the President from the streets.",
        "It is emphatically referred to as Go Home Quota. We are ready to unite in an all-party government and before that the President should step down, Nalin Bandara, a member of United People's Shakti, told the House.",
        "He mentioned the above during the debate on regulations under the Foreign Exchange Act held on Tuesday 05th in the Parliament.",
        "All of the country's current problems were created by President Gotabaya Rajapaksa and his government.",
        "Energy Minister visited Qatar last week regarding fuel import. Only after going. He said he was told that he could not import fuel from Qatar",
        "Power Minister Kanchana Wijesekara who intervened during this should not socialize the wrong thing. We visited at the invitation of the President of Qatar.",
        "Attention was paid to the sectors such as fuel and gas which are currently under crisis in the country.",
        "It has only been clearly mentioned that petrol and jet fuel will not be supplied. However, Qatar has indicated that it exports diesel, lubricants and lubricants. So he said that wrong things should not be socialized",
        "Nalin Fernando who continued to address.. is mentioned in relation to fuel import. There is talk of finding a solution to the problem by keeping the originator of all crises as the leader.",
        "They act against the policy. President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, who intensified the crises in such a way that the country is on fire, cannot solve any problems under the leadership.",
        "It is unacceptable for the ruling party to mention that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has a Lok Sabha. 69 lakh people are on the streets, cursing the President. People's trust in the government is seen at 3 percent.",
        "Prepared to form an all-party government under the direction of Mahanayake Theras. But the architect of the crisis, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, must step down. He said that the President should respect the aspirations of the people of the country and step down."
      ],
